definition.value: Lipid IVA glycosylated with four 3-deoxy-D-manno-octulosonic acid (KDO) residues.

label.value: EC 5.3.3.* (intramolecular oxidase transposing C=C bonds) inhibitor

definition.value: An EC 5.3.* (intramolecular oxidoreductase) inhibitor that inhibits the action of any such enzyme that transposes C=C bonds (EC 5.3.3.*).
A 3-oxo-5beta-steroid formed from 11-deoxycorticosterone by reduction across the C4-C5 double bond.
An EC 5.3.3.* (intramolecular oxidase transposing C=C bonds) inhibitor that interferes with the action of a cholestenol Delta-isomerase (EC 5.3.3.5).
A fatty acid anion 3:0 that is the conjugate base of 3-mercaptopropanoic acid.
A dicarboxylic acid dianion obtained by deprotonation of both carboxy groups of 3-methyladipic acid.
A quinic acid that is the 3-O-feruloyl derivative of D-quinic acid.
A 3-oxo-5beta-steroid formed from aldosterone by reduction across the C4-C5 double bond.
A monocarboxylic acid that is acetic acid substituted by a (pyridin-3-yl) group. It is a metabolite of nicotine and other tobacco alkaloids.
The (2S,3R)-stereoisomer of 2,3-dihydroxybutanoic acid.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the  conjugate base of 4-guanidinobutanoic acid.
An  androstanoid that is (5alpha)-androst-3-ene substituted by an oxo group at position 5.
An amino fatty acid anion that is the  conjugate base of 5-aminopentanoic acid.
A  hydroxy monocarboxylic acid that is furan substituted by a hydroxy group at position 5 and a carboxy group at position 2 respectively.
A dicarboxylic acid monoester that the monomethyl ester of  glutaric acid.
A monoglyceride in which the acyl group contains a total of 20 carbon atoms and 5 double bonds at unspecified positions.
A monoacylglycerol 20:5 in which the acyl group specified at position 2 is (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-eicosapentaenoyl.
A member of the class of hydroxycyclohexanones that is 4-hydroxycyclohexanone carrying a gem-dimethyl group at position 2 and an additional methyl substituent at position 6 (the 4R,6R-diastereomer).
The (2S)-stereoisomer of 2,3,4,5-tetrahydrodipicolinic acid.
A member of the class of cyclohexanones that is cyclohexane-1,4-dionecarrying a gem-dimethyl group at position 2 and an additional methyl substituent at position 6 (the R-enantiomer).
An alpha-amino-acid residue derived from cysteinyl-aspartic acid.
A bacterial hopanoid obtained by addition of an adenosyl group across the double bond of hopene.
A member of the class of azabicycloalkanes that is 1-azabicyclo[3.2.0]heptan-7-one substituted at positions 3 and 6 by (2-aminoethyl)thio and ethyl groups respectively.
A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of TDP-beta-L-rhamnose; major species at pH 7.3.
A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of TDP-actinospectose; major species at pH 7.3.
An amino cyclitol glycoside that is (1R,2S,3S,4S,5S,6R)-2-amino-1,3,4,6-tetrahydroxy-5-(methylamino)cyclohexane in which the hydroxy group at position 1 is glycosylated by a heptapyranosyl residue.
A phosphatidylcholine 28:1 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are decanoyl and (9Z-octadecenoyl respectively.

Either of the two diastereoisomers of 1-acetyl-4-(4-{[2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-2-(1H-imidazol-1-ylmethyl)-1,3-dioxolan-4-yl]methoxy}phenyl)piperazine in which the imidazol-1-ylmethyl group and the aryloxymethyl group are in a cis relationship to each other - i.e. they are both on the same side of the plane of the dioxolane ring. The antifungal drug ketoconazole is a racemic mixture of the two cis diastereoisomers.
An acyl-CoA(4-) oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 3-oxochol-4-en-24-oyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
An acyl-CoA(4-) oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 3-oxochola-4,22-dien-24-oyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
An acyl-CoA(4-) oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 3-oxocholesta-4,24-dien-26-oyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A phosphatidylcholine 30:2 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are (9Z)-hexadecenoyl and (9Z)-tetradecenoyl respectively.
A phosphatidylcholine 40:3 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are eicosanoyl and (11Z,14Z,17Z)-eicosatrienoyl respectively.
Organonitrogen compounds containing an aliphatic nitrogen that have significant antifungal properties.
A  phosphatidylcholine 42:2 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are hexadecanoyl and (5Z,9Z)-hexacosadienoyl respectively.
A polyunsaturated fatty acid that is hexacosanoic acid carrying double bonds at positions 5 and 9 respectively (the 5Z,9Z-isomer).
A compound that has significant antifungal properties whose structure contains an imidazole moiety.
A mononitrophenol that is 2-nitrophenol and its derivatives resulting from substitution of one or more of the hydrogens attached to the benzene ring by a non-nitro group.
A phosphatidylcholine 42:4 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are (6Z,9Z,12Z)-octadecatrienoyl and (15Z)-tetracosenoyl respectively.
A phosphatidylcholine O-30:2 in which the alkyl and acyl group specified at positions 1 and 2 are (9Z)-hexadecenyl and (9Z)-tetradecenoyl respectively.

A phosphatidylcholine O-32:2 in which the alkyl and acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are (9Z)-hexadecenyl and (9Z)-hexadecenoyl respectively.
A member of the class of triazole that has significant antifungal properties.
A phosphatidylcholine O-34:3 in which the alkyl and acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are hexadecyl and (6Z,9Z,12Z)-octadecatrienoyl respectively.
A member of the class of triazoles that is 1,2,4-triazole which is substituted at position 1 by a 1-(p-chlorophenyl)-3-hydroxy-4,4-dimethylpent-1-en-2-yl group.

A (1E)-1-(4-chlorophenyl)-4,4-dimethyl-2-(1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)pent-1-en-3-ol that has R configuration at the chiral centre. It is the enantiomer of the fungicide and plant growth retardant uniconazole-P; the fungicide and plant growth retardant uniconazole is the racemic mixture comprising equimolar amounts of (R)-uniconazole and uniconazole-P.
